content:
An OmniScript is an omnichannel customer engagement and business tool built on the Salesforce platform. It allows you to craft dynamic customer interactions without code, deploy to multiple channels and devices, and define a script once with seamless integration to enterprise applications and data.

You can create OmniScripts to guide users through sales and service processes with fast, personalized responses.

Lightning Web Component OmniScripts enable you to enhance an existing OmniScript element or add custom functionality using custom Lightning web components.

Classic OmniScript Designer allows you to create OmniScripts when an element, property, or functionality solves a project requirement that cannot be resolved in the LWC OmniScript Designer.

OmniScript Best Practices should be followed to enhance performance and usability.

You can create Multi-Language OmniScripts by allowing a single OmniScript to run in multiple languages using Salesforce custom labels.

Advanced Configuration for OmniScript Form Elements enables you to work with elements that allow users to input information, search for record information, select options, create records, edit records, and delete records.

OmniScript Data and External Integrations handle data and external integrations through Action, Group, and Input elements using Omnistudio Data Mappers, Integration Procedures, HTTP Actions, and Apex.

Administering, Deploying, and Launching OmniScripts involves importing, versioning, launching, and deploying OmniScripts to various platforms.

OmniScript Element Reference provides explanations of the different elements that can be added to an OmniScript, including Omnistudio Data Mapper actions.

OmniScript ReadMe Reference lists the Lightning web components ReadMes available for OmniScripts.
title: Understanding OmniScripts in Salesforce
